
Ryoku Linux installer (live)  --  @RYOKU_VERSION@ (@RYOKU_COMMIT@)

The graphical installer starts automatically on the first console. This serial
or secondary console is a plain root shell. To run the installer here, set the
RYOKU_* answers and run `ryoku-install` (see /usr/share/ryoku for the payload).

Wiping a whole disk that already holds partitions also needs
RYOKU_WIPE_CONFIRMED=1 (the graphical installer's typed ERASE step); a blank
disk installs without it.

